  "title": "IT Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>- Project planning and management</p>\n<p>- Plan Schedule and Time management (policies, procedures and documentation for planning, developing, managing, executing, and controlling the project schedule)</p>\n<p>- Stakeholder/Vendor, Communications and Risk Management</p>\n<p>- Resource plan / Project LOE (Level of Efforts) management</p>\n<p>- Organize and participate in vendor/project meetings</p>\n<p>- Create a detailed project management plan and other project documents</p>\n<p>- Provide solutions to project-related issues</p>\n<p>- Define the project’s scope, milestones and deadlines</p>\n<p>- Understand IT management policy, quality management policy and security guidelines to ensure the development processes, procedure and systems are designed to comply with these policies and guidelines</p>\n<p>- Track project performance, perform any other relevant, project-related duties when needed</p>\n<p>- Minimum 5 years of relevant working experiences in Project Management</p>\n<p>- Experience in handling projects involving Cloud, Design Thinking, web technologies, software development, system integration, and manage changes will be strongly preferred</p>\n<p>- In-depth experience in business processes and skill in business analysis techniques</p>\n<p>- Ability to construct/maintain a project budget and manage project accordingly</p>\n<p>- Diploma/Bachelor's degree in the fields of computer science/IT or engineering for technical project managers</p>\n<p>- Solid technical background, with understanding or hands-on experience in software development, and web technologies</p>\n<p>- Excellent vendor management, manage communication with external and internal stakeholders</p>\n<p>- Solid organizational skills including attention to detail and multi-tasking skills</p>\n<p>- Actively participates in process improvement discussions aimed at identifying bottlenecks and streamlining processes</p>\n<p>- Ability to work unsupervised, with little management oversight</p>",
